<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,1436,1494,1520]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">The group comprises 1 species. It is characterised by the following 6 character states; apomorphic character</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,432,1538,1564]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">states marked by (apo.):</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,789,1580,1606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- forewing extremely broad and rounded (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,746,1624,1650]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- forewing and hindwing dark brown (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- ampulla slightly asymmetrical, round, circular; right one teardrop-shaped, left one with a small dorsal hump (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,1010,1753,1779]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- digitus prominent, slightly asymmetrical, left one slightly longer;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,717,1796,1822]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- pollex small, broad, and rounded (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,572,1839,1865]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- valve longer than wide; and</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1494,1908]" box="[151,957,1882,1908]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">- phallus very narrow and long, smoothly curving subapically.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
